<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1977-06-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1977-06-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="199" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                        <head>199. Memorandum From Director of Central Intelligence <persName corresp="#p_TS_1">Turner</persName> to Vice President <persName corresp="#p_MWF_1">Mondale</persName><note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d199fn1">Source: Central Intelligence Agency, Office of the
                                Director of Central Intelligence, Job 80M00165A, Box 5, Folder 130:
                                C-7: Chile. Secret. Drafted [<hi rend="italic">less than 1 line not
                                    declassified</hi>] on July 1, concurrence by Wells on July 2.
                                Printed from a copy which indicates that it was sent on July
                                5.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1977-06-27T23:59:59-05:00" notBefore="1977-06-27T00:00:00-05:00">undated</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <list type="subject">
                            <head>SUBJECT</head>
                            <item>Recent Activities of <persName corresp="#p_FE_1">Eduardo
                                    Frei</persName></item>
                        </list>
                        <p>1. Attached<note n="2" xml:id="d199fn2">See <ref target="#d200">Document
                                    200</ref>.</note> is a memorandum on the recent activities of
                            the former President of Chile, <persName corresp="#p_FE_1">Eduardo
                                Frei</persName>. This might be of particular interest to you in the
                            light of your late May discussion with him.<note n="3" xml:id="d199fn3">See <ref target="#d194">Document 194</ref>.</note></p>
                        <p>This subject will also be treated in a forthcoming issue [<hi rend="italic">less than 1 line not declassified</hi>].<note n="4" xml:id="d199fn4">July 7, 1977. (Carter Library, National Security
                                Affairs, <persName corresp="#p_BZ_1">Brzezinski</persName> Material,
                                    [<hi rend="italic">less than 1 line not declassified</hi>] File,
                                Box 3, 7/7/77-7/15/77)</note></p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><persName corresp="#p_TS_1"><hi rend="strong">Stansfield
                                        Turner</hi></persName><note n="5" xml:id="d199fn5">A
                                    notation indicating that <persName corresp="#p_TS_1">Turner</persName> signed the memorandum was typed above his
                                    name.</note></signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>